**************************************************************
Setup Instructions to install Blog server on an Ubuntu Machine

1. Install Mongo DB (v3.0.X) on the Database server and start the mongod instance
   Instructions to install and start mongodb on Ubuntu
   https://docs.mongodb.org/v3.0/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-ubuntu/

2. Install NodeJS and npm package manager
   sudo apt-get install nodejs
   sudo apt-get install npm

   or Follow the below link to install nodejs and npm

   https://nodejs.org/en/download/package-manager/

3. Extract the blog_server.zip that you have downloaded

4. Go to the directory
   cd blog_server

5. Execute the below command, This will install all the dependent packages
   npm install

6. Open blog.conf file and fill in the necessary details

7. Execute the following command to start the blog server
   nohup node blog_server.js > blog.log &

   That's it your blog server should be up and running :)

***************************************************************

